  <para><emphasis role="bold">Description:</emphasis></para>

  <para>This is the most important CGI included with &name-icinga;. It allows you to view the current status of all hosts and services that
  are being monitored. The status CGI can produce two main types of output - a status overview of all host groups (or a particular host
  group) and a detailed view of all services (or those associated with a particular host).</para>

  <para><emphasis role="bold">Authorization Requirements:</emphasis></para>

  <itemizedlist>
    <listitem>
      <para>If you are <link xlink:href="configcgi#authorized_for_all_hosts"> <emphasis>authorized for all hosts</emphasis> </link> you can
      view all hosts <emphasis role="bold">and</emphasis> all services.</para>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
      <para>If you are <link xlink:href="configcgi#authorized_for_all_services"> <emphasis>authorized for all services</emphasis> </link>
      you can view all services.</para>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
      <para>If you are an <emphasis>authenticated contact</emphasis> you can view all hosts and services for which you are a contact.</para>
    </listitem>
  </itemizedlist>

  <para><anchor xml:id="cgis-statusmap_cgi" /><emphasis role="bold">Status Map CGI</emphasis></para>

  <informaltable frame="none">
    <tgroup cols="1">
